5. Part D – Open Source vs Proprietary Software

| Feature       | Open Source (Firefox) | Proprietary Software (Chrome) |
| ------------- | --------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Cost          | Free                  | Free                          |
| Source Code   | Open                  | Mostly closed                 |
| Flexibility   | High                  | Limited                       |
| Customization | Allowed               | Restricted                    |
| Control       | Community-driven      | Corporate-controlled          |

Open-source software like Firefox provides greater transparency and user control compared to proprietary alternatives.

